PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_0_DESC: 100% theoretical contact area between propeller boss and shaft, as read from plans and disregarding oil grooves.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_1_DESC: Mean outer diameter of propeller hub at the axial position corresponding to dPM.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_2_DESC: Diameter of propeller shaft at the mid-point of the taper in the axial direction.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_4_DESC: C = 1 for turbines, geared diesel engines, electrical drives and direct-drive reciprocating internal combustion engines with a hydraulic, electromagnetic or high elasticity coupling. C = 1,2 for diesel engines having couplings other than those specified above.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_6_DESC: Continuous thrust developed for free running ship.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_7_DESC: Safety factor against friction slip at 35°C.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_8_DESC: Half taper of propeller shaft (for instance: taper = 1/15, Î¸ =1/30).
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_9_DESC: Coefficient of friction between mating surfaces.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_10_DESC: Value of the modulus of elasticity of boss material.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_11_DESC: Value of the modulus of elasticity of shaft material,.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_14_DESC: Value of the minimum yield strength (ReH), or 0,2% proof stress (Rp 0,2), of propeller boss material.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_15_DESC: Coefficient of linear expansion of boss material.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_16_DESC: Coefficient of linear expansion of shaft material.
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_FORMULA_3: Continuous thrust developed for free running ship [N]
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_FORMULA_8: Corresponding minimum surface pressure at temperature [MPa]
PROPELLER_BV_LEDEND_LABEL_FORMULA_11: Corresponding maximum permissible pull-up length at 0°C [mm]
